DATA CLOUD
Associate Permission Sets with Data Spaces

Data Cloud standard permission sets are associated with the default data space when Data Cloud is enabled. To give access to other data spaces, change the data space permission set it's associated with, or create a permission set.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To manage permission sets:	Manage Profiles and Permission Sets
NOTE This content applies to orgs that have enabled enhanced security data spaces. How you secure your data using permission sets depends on whether you have legacy data spaces or enhanced security data spaces in your org.

When enhanced security is enabled, the default data space is associated with standard Data Cloud permission sets, except the Data Cloud Admin and Data Space Marketing Admin permission sets. All other data spaces must be manually associated to permission sets, including to the standard permission sets. Admin users can view features and feature setup, but can’t access data unless the data space is associated with the admin permission set.

In Setup, search for Permission Sets and select Permission Sets.
Select the permission set you want to associate with a data space.
Under Apps, select Data Cloud Data Space Management.
On Data Space Scopes, click Edit.
Select one or more data spaces to associate them to the permission set.
Click Save.
To add feature permissions within an associated data space, click a data space name.
Click Edit.
Select View or Customize on features that should be viewable or customizable by users assigned in the data space associated with the permission set.
